<emphasis bold="true" box="[1368,1395,151,175]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">73</emphasis>
: 76 (71–80) wide at level of anus. Setae ZV1, ZV3 and JV4 on integument surrounding ventri-anal shield. Setae JV5 smooth; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,178,220,244]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">41</emphasis>
: 43 (37–49) long.
</paragraph>
<caption pageId="1" pageNumber="66" startId="1.[151,269,1975,1999]" targetBox="[161,1432,312,1958]" targetPageId="1">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1975,2033]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,317,1975,1999]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">FIGURES 1–7</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Demite, Lofego &amp; Feres" authorityYear="2007" box="[332,613,1976,1999]" class="Arachnida" family="Phytoseiidae" genus="Amblyseius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paulofariensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[332,613,1976,1999]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">Amblyseius paulofariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[621,707,1975,1999]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[621,707,1975,1999]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
1–5. Female. 1. Dorsal shield, 2. Ventral idiosoma, 3. Chelicera, 4. Spermatheca, 5. Leg IV (genu, tibia and basitarsus). 6–7. Male. 6, Ventri-anal shield, 7. Chelicera.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,1185]" box="[199,1360,151,175]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis box="[199,304,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Chelicera</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[319,383,152,175]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1975,1999]" captionTargetBox="[161,1432,312,1958]" captionTargetId="figure-103@1.[151,1436,301,1967]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. Amblyseius paulofariensis sp. nov. 1–5. Female. 1. Dorsal shield, 2. Ventral idiosoma, 3. Chelicera, 4. Spermatheca, 5. Leg IV (genu, tibia and basitarsus). 6–7. Male. 6, Ventri-anal shield, 7. Chelicera." pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Movable digit 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[561,587,151,175]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">28</emphasis>
: 28 (27–29) with three teeth, fixed digit 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1022,1048,151,175]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">24</emphasis>
: 25 (23–26) with 8–10 teeth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,1185]" box="[199,773,183,207]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis box="[199,338,184,207]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Spermatheca</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[353,418,184,207]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1975,1999]" captionTargetBox="[161,1432,312,1958]" captionTargetId="figure-103@1.[151,1436,301,1967]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. Amblyseius paulofariensis sp. nov. 1–5. Female. 1. Dorsal shield, 2. Ventral idiosoma, 3. Chelicera, 4. Spermatheca, 5. Leg IV (genu, tibia and basitarsus). 6–7. Male. 6, Ventri-anal shield, 7. Chelicera." pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Cervix tubular; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[607,620,183,207]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">7</emphasis>
: 8 (7–9) long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,1185]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis box="[199,249,216,239]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Legs</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[264,329,216,239]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1975,1999]" captionTargetBox="[161,1432,312,1958]" captionTargetId="figure-103@1.[151,1436,301,1967]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. Amblyseius paulofariensis sp. nov. 1–5. Female. 1. Dorsal shield, 2. Ventral idiosoma, 3. Chelicera, 4. Spermatheca, 5. Leg IV (genu, tibia and basitarsus). 6–7. Male. 6, Ventri-anal shield, 7. Chelicera." pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). With setaceous macrosetae of the following lengths: Sge I 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[979,1005,215,239]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">29</emphasis>
: 31 (29–33), Sge II 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1223,1250,215,239]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">26</emphasis>
: 29 (26–31), Sge III 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[184,211,247,271]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">34</emphasis>
: 32 (29–34), Sti III 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[423,449,247,271]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">24</emphasis>
: 24 (22–27), Sge IV 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[675,702,247,271]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">53</emphasis>
: 53 (51–55), Sti IV 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[916,943,247,271]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">38</emphasis>
: 40 (38–43), St IV 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1149,1176,247,271]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">51</emphasis>
: 52 (48–56). Chaetotactic formula of genu II: 2-2/0-2/0-1 and genu III: 1-2/1-2/0-1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,1185]" box="[198,680,312,335]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis box="[198,253,312,335]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[267,400,312,335]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1975,1999]" captionTargetBox="[161,1432,312,1958]" captionTargetId="figure-103@1.[151,1436,301,1967]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. Amblyseius paulofariensis sp. nov. 1–5. Female. 1. Dorsal shield, 2. Ventral idiosoma, 3. Chelicera, 4. Spermatheca, 5. Leg IV (genu, tibia and basitarsus). 6–7. Male. 6, Ventri-anal shield, 7. Chelicera." pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Figs 6 and 7</figureCitation>
) (
<specimenCount box="[423,554,312,335]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" type="generic">5 specimens</specimenCount>
measured).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,1185]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis box="[199,285,344,367]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Dorsum</emphasis>
. Dorsal shield smooth, with a few striae anterolaterally, 236 (231–240) long, 170 (166–171) wide at level of s4; setae: j1 17 (14–19), j3 26 (24–28), j4 6 (5–6), j5 5 (5), j6 6 (6–7), J2 9 (8–9), J5 6 (6–7), z2 9 (8–9), z4 9 (8–9), z5 5 (5), Z1 7 (7–8), Z4 37 (34–41), Z5 60 (56–64), 
<geoCoordinate box="[661,718,408,431]" degrees="4" direction="south" minutes="30" orientation="latitude" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" precision="925" value="-4.5">s4 30</geoCoordinate>
(28–32), 
<geoCoordinate box="[823,884,408,431]" degrees="2" direction="south" minutes="10" orientation="latitude" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" precision="925" value="-2.1666667">S2 10</geoCoordinate>
(9–11), 
<geoCoordinate box="[976,1036,408,431]" degrees="4" direction="south" minutes="11" orientation="latitude" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" precision="925" value="-4.1833334">S4 11</geoCoordinate>
(11), 
<geoCoordinate box="[1100,1161,408,431]" degrees="5" direction="south" minutes="11" orientation="latitude" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" precision="925" value="-5.1833334">S5 11</geoCoordinate>
(10–11), r3 11 (11), R1 9 (8–10). All setae smooth, except Z4 and Z5 which are serrated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,1185]" box="[199,707,472,495]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis box="[199,304,472,495]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Peritreme</emphasis>
. Extending forward to the level of j1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,1185]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis box="[199,267,504,527]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Venter</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[283,349,504,527]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1975,1999]" captionTargetBox="[161,1432,312,1958]" captionTargetId="figure-103@1.[151,1436,301,1967]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. Amblyseius paulofariensis sp. nov. 1–5. Female. 1. Dorsal shield, 2. Ventral idiosoma, 3. Chelicera, 4. Spermatheca, 5. Leg IV (genu, tibia and basitarsus). 6–7. Male. 6, Ventri-anal shield, 7. Chelicera." pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Sternogenital shield smooth; ventri-anal shield subtriangular, mostly smooth, striated from anterior extremity to level of JV1; 99 (95–103) long and 131 (125–136) wide at anterior corners, with three pairs of pre-anal setae, one distinct pair of pores posterior and mediad to bases of JV2, and four other smaller pairs of lyrifissures.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,1185]" box="[199,687,600,623]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis box="[199,346,600,623]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Spermadactyl</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[360,425,600,623]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1975,1999]" captionTargetBox="[161,1432,312,1958]" captionTargetId="figure-103@1.[151,1436,301,1967]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. Amblyseius paulofariensis sp. nov. 1–5. Female. 1. Dorsal shield, 2. Ventral idiosoma, 3. Chelicera, 4. Spermatheca, 5. Leg IV (genu, tibia and basitarsus). 6–7. Male. 6, Ventri-anal shield, 7. Chelicera." pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Shaft 15 (14–16) long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,1185]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis box="[151,201,632,655]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Legs</emphasis>
. With setaceous macrosetae of the following lengths: Sge I 24 (23–26), Sge II 24 (22–25), Sge III 24 (21–25), Sti III 20 (18–21), Sge IV 34 (31–36), Sti IV 28 (26–32), St IV 45 (41–47). Chaetotactic formula of genu II and genu III as in females.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="67" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,1185]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,327,746,770]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to the 
<typeStatus box="[674,720,746,769]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">type</typeStatus>
locality “Estação Ecológica de Paulo de Faria”, a protected natural area in the northwest of 
<collectingRegion box="[409,579,781,804]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">São Paulo State</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[589,658,781,804]" name="Brazil" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Brazil</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="67" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,1185]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,308,815,839]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Demite, Lofego &amp; Feres" authorityYear="2007" box="[322,602,816,839]" class="Arachnida" family="Phytoseiidae" genus="Amblyseius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paulofariensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[322,602,816,839]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Amblyseius paulofariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[609,695,815,839]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[609,695,815,839]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
was the most abundant species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A.Berlese" authorityYear="1916" box="[1064,1200,816,839]" class="Arachnida" family="Phytoseiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Phytoseiidae</taxonomicName>
on 
<taxonomicName box="[1240,1390,816,839]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Acalypha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="diversifolia">
<emphasis box="[1240,1256,816,839]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1269,1390,816,839]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">diversifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[151,292,850,873]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Actinostemon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="communis">
<emphasis box="[151,167,850,873]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[184,292,850,873]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">communis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, representing 35% and 44% of all the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A.Berlese" authorityYear="1916" box="[732,868,850,873]" class="Arachnida" family="Phytoseiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Phytoseiidae</taxonomicName>
collected on those hosts respectively (Feres 
<emphasis box="[1372,1422,850,873]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">et al</emphasis>
., unpublished data). Since this is such an abundant species, studies should be conducted to evaluate its predatory potential for control of pest mites of agriculture. The &quot;Estação Ecológica de Paulo de Faria&quot; is an area of great ecological importance, being the largest protected natural area of the northwest of State of 
<collectingRegion box="[961,1072,954,977]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
, considering that this region possesses only 3% of the original natural vegetation.
</paragraph>
